HEADWORD: Boost
<hw>Boost</hw> <pr>(b⟦oomac⟧st)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Boosted</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. &
vb. n.</pos> <conjf>Boosting</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Cf.
<er>Boast</er>, <pos>v. i.</pos>]</ety> <def>To lift or push from behind
(one who is endeavoring to climb); to push up; hence, to assist in
overcoming obstacles, or in making advancement.</def> <mark>[Colloq. U.
S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

